Tesla `dashcam-mp4.js` and `dashcam.proto` are vendored here from
https://github.com/teslamotors/dashcam (checked 2025-06-25) for the
documented purpose of decoding SEI metadata in Tesla dashcam MP4 clips.

LICENSE STATUS: The upstream repository does NOT publish a LICENSE file.
Issue https://github.com/teslamotors/dashcam/issues/6 tracks community
requests for a license; it is unresolved at the time of this vendoring.

See `docs/adr/0016-vendored-tesla-dashcam-mp4-for-sei.md` for the full
rationale, alternatives considered, and update procedure once Tesla
publishes an explicit license. Pragmatic acceptance: Tesla published
this code as the only documented mechanism for interop with their own
dashcam format, implying permission for that interop purpose.

If you are a downstream user with strict license requirements, remove
`static/vendor/dashcam-mp4/` and disable the dashcam playback overlay
until a clean-room re-implementation lands (tracked follow-up; see
ADR-0016).